  <div class="detail-section">
    <h3>Problem the framework addresses</h3>
    <p>
      Psychedelics often produce experiences rated as deeply meaningful while increasing neural signal diversity (‚Äúentropy‚Äù proxies). At the same time, active inference / free‚Äëenergy accounts emphasize uncertainty reduction as adaptive.
      E.M.E.R.G.E+ resolves this by separating <strong>two kinds of meaning emergence</strong> that have different entropy signatures.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="detail-section">
    <h3>Core idea</h3>
    <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
      <li><strong>Routine meaning</strong>: emerges during everyday coherent functioning via gradual entropy reduction.</li>
      <li><strong>Transformative meaning</strong>: emerges via a <strong>biphasic trajectory</strong> during critical transitions (e.g., psychedelic sessions): transient entropy elevation (onset/peak) followed by deep entropy reduction (descent/integration).</li>
      <li><strong>Formalization</strong>: coupled differential equations specify emotional entropy dynamics, arousal/energy terms, and boundary conditions across timescales (seconds‚Äìminutes vs hours‚Äìdays).</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="detail-section">
    <h3>Computational demonstrations (illustrative, not empirical)</h3>
    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p style="margin:0 0 10px 0;">
        Simulations are mathematical demonstrations using hypothetical parameters (Python; Euler integration; seed = 2025). They illustrate qualitative behavior and internal consistency.
      </p>
      <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
        <li><strong>Routine demo (10 s):</strong> emotional entropy proxy H<sub>e</sub> 0.000 ‚Üí ‚àí0.714 while routine meaning M<sub>r</sub> 0.210 ‚Üí 0.922.</li>
        <li><strong>Transformative demo (0‚Äì8 h):</strong> H<sub>e</sub> peaks at 0.895 (‚âà 2 h) then drops to ‚àí0.455 by 8 h (below baseline), with normalized cumulative transformative meaning reaching 1.000.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="detail-section">
    <h3>Falsifiable predictions (examples)</h3>
    <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
      <li>Neural signal diversity measures (e.g., Lempel‚ÄìZiv complexity) should <strong>increase at peak</strong> and then <strong>decrease post‚Äëpeak</strong>, potentially undershooting baseline in a subset of individuals.</li>
      <li>The magnitude of the <strong>post‚Äëpeak decrease</strong> should correlate with retrospective meaning ratings (e.g., MEQ30).</li>
      <li>Phase‚Äë2 dynamics (descent/integration) may be more outcome‚Äërelevant than peak intensity, motivating monitoring windows of ~8‚Äì12 hours and integration supports during descent.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="detail-section">
    <h3>Status &amp; open science</h3>
    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p style="margin:0;">
        Current status is explicitly theoretical (n = 0). The manuscript specifies operationalizations and validation protocols, and commits to sharing simulation code/outputs and preregistered empirical tests to support disconfirmable science.
