  <div class="detail-section">
    <h3>Core claim</h3>
    <p>
      Beauty filters do something psychologically ‚Äúspecial‚Äù: they create an <strong>intrapersonal ideal</strong> (a more attractive version of the self) that is highly accessible, self‚Äëresembling, and socially reinforced. The paradox is that a tool adopted to feel better can, over time, intensify dissatisfaction and avoidance.
    </p>
