      <li><strong>Algorithmic enhancement</strong> of facial features (observable modifications).</li>
      <li><strong>Actual‚Äìdigital self‚Äëdiscrepancy</strong> (filtered self becomes an ‚Äúideal self‚Äù).</li>
      <li><strong>Perceptual recalibration</strong> (filtered self becomes the perceptual baseline).</li>
      <li><strong>Self‚Äëobjectification</strong> and heightened appearance monitoring.</li>
      <li><strong>Filter dependence</strong> as avoidance/safety behavior (reluctance to appear unfiltered).</li>
      <li><strong>Downstream psychosocial outcomes</strong> (e.g., distress, depression/eating‚Äërisk pathways, social anxiety) with explicit notes on evidence vs theory.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="detail-section">
    <h3>Computational formalization (examples)</h3>
    <div class="highlight-box">
      <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
        <li><strong>Body dissatisfaction trajectory:</strong> D(t) = Œ¥<sub>0</sub> + Œ≤<sub>1</sub>F(t) + Œ≤<sub>2</sub>S(t) + Œ≤<sub>3</sub>F(t)√óS(t) (+ Œµ)</li>
        <li><strong>Recalibration threshold:</strong> P(filtered baseline) = 1 / (1 + e<sup>‚àík(F(t) ‚àí Œ∏)</sup>)</li>
        <li><strong>Dependence via negative reinforcement:</strong> V(filter) = ‚àíŒª √ó E[distress | unfiltered]</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="detail-section">
    <h3>Testable predictions (high-level)</h3>
    <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
      <li><strong>Behavior:</strong> develop and validate an Actual‚ÄëDigital Self‚ÄëDiscrepancy Scale (ADSDS); test 4‚Äì6 week exposure effects on self‚Äëimage ratings; model 6‚Äì12+ month dependence trajectories.</li>
      <li><strong>EEG:</strong> larger LPP to filtered self‚Äëimages (emotional salience), rightward FAA shifts during unfiltered self‚Äëviewing (withdrawal motivation), with early face encoding (e.g., N170) predicted to be less affected than late evaluative components.</li>
